      "parameters": {
        "color": 4,
        "width": 460,
        "height": 1220,
        "content": "### ### Step 3: `Get Invoice Template` ‚Äî Load Google Doc  \nLoads a static Google Docs template containing placeholder values.\n\n- üßæ **Template URL**: [Copy This Template](https://docs.google.com/document/d/18n0HTqabDldi7fVbhbI1aG12qbFWsjyTXdduwDDOUu8/edit)\n- **Required Placeholders** in the document:\n  ```\n  FromCompany#\n  ToCompany#\n  Terms#\n  Invoice#\n  Description#\n  Amount#\n  ```\n\n> üîë **Credentials Required**:  \n> Connect to **Google Docs OAuth2 API** in n8n.\n\n---\n\n### ### Step 4: `Create New Doc` ‚Äî Make Invoice File  \nCreates a new Google Doc by duplicating the invoice template.\n\n- **Title Format**: `Invoice: {{ $json.Invoice }}`\n- **Destination Folder ID**: `1TnDibwPPPUm3VbmETiqWDVhtaUTLJ6mn`  \n  *(You can change this to your own Google Drive folder)*\n\n> üîê Make sure your Google Docs credential has write access to this folder.\n\n---\n\n### ### Step 5: `Merge` ‚Äî Combine Data  \nMerges the loaded document and spreadsheet row together for downstream updates.\n\n---"
      },
      "typeVersion": 1
    },
